-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
& is a bitwise AND operator. 
Doing (num & 1) checks if the last bit (least significant bit) of the number is set.
If it is set, the number is odd, and if it is not set, it is even.
It is just a fast way to check if a number is even or odd.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
testcode/byte_order.cpp

bits xor-ed with themselves are always zero

XORing the same value twice restores the original

The Bitwise XOR (exclusive or) performs a logical XOR function, which is equivalent 
to adding two bits and discarding the carry.
